---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
import '../../styles/course.css';
import LessonPage from '../../components/course/LessonPage';
import GatePanel from '../../components/assessment/GatePanel';
---

<BaseLayout title="Context Length Means Token Capacity">
  <LessonPage lessonId="L04" client:load>

    <div class="lesson-section">
      <div class="section-label">Question</div>
      <div class="lesson-question">What does context length measure?</div>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-section">
      <div class="section-label">Intuition</div>
      <p>
        The model has a maximum number of tokens it can process at once. This is the <strong>context length</strong> (or context window).
      </p>
      <p>
        Both the prompt and the generated output share this budget. If the context length is 8,192 tokens and your prompt uses 6,000, there are only 2,192 tokens left for generation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Context length is not measured in characters or words. It is measured in tokens, because that is the unit the model operates on.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-section">
      <div class="section-label">Toy Example</div>
      <div class="toy-example">
        <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--ink-tertiary); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
          A model with context length = 10 tokens:
        </p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 3px; margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
          <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; background: var(--sem-token-bg); border: 1px solid var(--sem-token-dim); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--sem-token);">The</div>
          <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; background: var(--sem-token-bg); border: 1px solid var(--sem-token-dim); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--sem-token);">·cat</div>
          <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; background: var(--sem-token-bg); border: 1px solid var(--sem-token-dim); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--sem-token);">·sat</div>
          <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; background: var(--sem-token-bg); border: 1px solid var(--sem-token-dim); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--sem-token);">·on</div>
          <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; background: var(--sem-token-bg); border: 1px solid var(--sem-token-dim); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--sem-token);">·the</div>
          <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; background: var(--sem-token-bg); border: 1px solid var(--sem-token-dim); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--sem-token);">·mat</div>
          <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; background: var(--sem-logits-bg); border: 1px solid var(--sem-logits-dim); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--sem-logits);">.</div>
          <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; border: 1px dashed var(--ink-ghost); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--ink-ghost);"></div>
          <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; border: 1px dashed var(--ink-ghost); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--ink-ghost);"></div>
          <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; border: 1px dashed var(--ink-ghost); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--ink-ghost);"></div>
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: var(--space-4); font-size: var(--text-xs); font-family: var(--font-mono);">
          <span style="color: var(--sem-token);">&#x25A0; prompt: 7 tokens</span>
          <span style="color: var(--ink-ghost);">&#x25A1; available: 3 tokens</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-section">
      <div class="section-label">Shapes</div>
      <div class="shape-card">
        <div>context_length: maximum number of tokens the model can process</div>
        <div>n_prompt + n_generated &#x2264; context_length</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-section">
      <div class="section-label">Math</div>
      <p>The only new math concept is a capacity constraint:</p>
      <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--sem-token); background: var(--surface-3); padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); margin: var(--space-3) 0; display: inline-block;">
        n_prompt + n_generated &#x2264; L
      </div>
      <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--ink-tertiary);">
        where L is the context length. Both the input and the output compete for the same budget.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-section">
      <div class="section-label">Implementation Hook</div>
      <div class="impl-hook">
        <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--ink-secondary);">
          Context length is set in the model's metadata and enforced at runtime.
          In <code>llama.cpp</code>, exceeding the context length results in an error or truncation, not a graceful degradation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-section">
      <div class="section-label">Performance Hook</div>
      <div class="perf-hook">
        <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--ink-secondary);">
          Longer context means more tokens for the model to process — more computation, more memory for storing intermediate results.
          Later, you will learn that attention cost grows with sequence length, and that the KV cache grows linearly with context used.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-section">
      <div class="section-label">Check Yourself</div>
      <GatePanel
        client:load
        lessonId="L04"
        gateStrength="soft"
        questions={[
          {
            id: 'L04-q1',
            type: 'single_choice',
            prompt: 'A model has context length 4096. Your prompt tokenizes to 3500 tokens. How many tokens can the model generate?',
            tag: 'math',
            choices: [
              { id: 'a', text: '4096', isCorrect: false },
              { id: 'b', text: '596', isCorrect: true },
              { id: 'c', text: '3500', isCorrect: false },
            ],
            explanation: '4096 - 3500 = 596 tokens remaining for generation. Prompt and output share the same budget.',
          },
        ]}
      />
    </div>

  </LessonPage>
</BaseLayout>
